			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">Ironically, after reading this installment, I started reading=
 "Handbook of Computer Crime Investigation: Forensic Tools and=
 Technology" by Eoghan Casey=2E The first chapter starts off by=
 presenting the "collect live evidence in memory" vs "power it=
 off immediately" debate, this very point is brought up=2E The last=
 argument against powering down the machine is "Finally, there is=
 the physical risk that the computer could be rigged to explode=
 if the power switch is toggled=2E" This is something I'm sure very=
 few of us have thought about=2E It would be trivial for someone=
 with a very rudimentary understanding of electronics to built a=
 device that monitored the power of the machine and caused any=
 number of Bad Things <tm> to happen upon power loss=2E I=
 appreciate the word of warning, and I hope this re-enforces it=2E=
 Always think before you act=2E=2E=2E Especially Scrap ;)

</span>
