			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">Mike Hargis:
""ala Limewire" - "aka Limewire" A friendly grammar catch for you chief."


Me:
No, "aka" stands for "also known as", where "a la" means "In the style or manner of".  

Chief saw a lime logo, so it's a pretty good indication that the kid was using Limewire in the context of snagging some movies.


Chief:
"I leaned over to get a better glimpse of the beautiful 17-inch widescreen display on the Apple Powerbook when a familiar logo caught my eye. A lime, ala Limewire."


Just a friendly grammar correction for YOU.  :)

</span>
