			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">The only IT room I have been a part of that had Halon, had many warning signs all over the place....

It said if you hear the alarm go off, get out of the room immediately...
The alarm consisted of bells, as well as a few mounted wall lights (like normal fire lights) that blinked 'Halon' when activated)...

It also said the halon would not start for a good 15-30 seconds after the warning... (so there is enough time to evacuate a decent sized room)

But it did clearly make it sound like one would not want to be hanging around in the Halon. 

